## 1. Project Identity & Scope

### 1.1 Project Overview

**JavaOopExercises** is an educational Java project designed to teach Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) principles through the implementation of a progressive banking system. Learners develop increasingly complex banking features, starting with basic class creation and advancing to inheritance, method overriding, collections, and system-wide reporting.

### 1.2 Project Scope (IN)

✅ **In Scope:**
- Creating core banking classes (BankAccount, SavingsAccount, CheckingAccount)
- Implementing OOP fundamentals: encapsulation, inheritance, polymorphism
- Building customer account management systems
- Tracking transaction histories
- Generating banking reports
- Progressive exercise completion from Exercise 1 through Exercise 8
- Demonstrating features in the `Main.main()` method via `System.out.println()`
- Single JVM execution environment with standard Java libraries only

### 1.3 Project Scope (OUT)

❌ **Out of Scope:**
- Database persistence or file I/O beyond in-memory operations
- Network communication or REST APIs
- UI/GUI implementations (console output only)
- Multi-threading or concurrency
- External framework dependencies (Spring, Hibernate, etc.)
- Deployment to production environments
- User authentication or authorization systems
- Real banking compliance or security protocols
- Third-party payment processing integrations

### 1.4 Target Audience

- Java learners (beginner to intermediate level)
- Students studying OOP concepts
- Self-paced learners or course participants
- Instructors/mentors reviewing student implementations

