## 3. Allowed Tech & Constraints

### 3.1 Technology Stack

| Category | Technology | Version | Notes |
|----------|-----------|---------|-------|
| **Language** | Java | 8+ (JDK 8 or higher) | No language version restrictions |
| **Build Tools** | None required for exercises | — | Plain Java compilation (javac) sufficient |
| **Libraries** | Java Standard Library only | — | `java.util.*`, `java.lang.*` permitted |
| **IDE / Editor** | VS Code + Extension Pack for Java | — | Official recommended environment |

### 3.2 Technical Constraints

- ✅ **Allowed:**
  - Standard Java class definition and inheritance
  - `java.util.ArrayList`, `java.util.LinkedList`, or similar Collections
  - Getter/setter methods
  - String concatenation and formatting
  - Basic arithmetic operations (double floating-point)
  - `System.out.println()` for console output
  - Exception handling with try-catch (optional, not required)

- ❌ **Forbidden:**
  - External JAR dependencies or Maven/Gradle configurations
  - Database connections (JDBC, JPA, etc.)
  - Reflection APIs
  - Serialization (unless for student exploration)
  - File I/O or stream operations
  - Lambdas or advanced functional programming constructs (unless studying Exercise 8+)
  - Static state or singleton patterns (except Main.main())

### 3.3 Performance & Scalability Constraints

- Maximum expected accounts per customer: 10–20 (in-memory)
- Maximum expected transactions per account: 100–200 (in-memory)
- All operations must complete in <100ms for demo purposes
- No optimization for production-scale scenarios required

